SFOS: bind /odm and /vendor/firmware_mnt into the bwrap sandbox.

The Adreno GPU driver libraries live on the /odm partition (separate ext4)
and the firmware on /vendor/firmware_mnt (vfat).  On kernel 4.14,
"--dev-bind / /" does NOT recursively include these submounts, so the
sandboxed WebProcess cannot load the GPU driver (blank screen).

Applies on top of webkit-bubblewrap-sfos-sandbox.patch.

--- a/Source/WebKit/UIProcess/Launcher/glib/BubblewrapLauncher.cpp	2026-06-05 15:27:42.887175694 +0000
+++ b/Source/WebKit/UIProcess/Launcher/glib/BubblewrapLauncher.cpp	2026-06-05 15:27:42.909175866 +0000
@@ -820,6 +820,15 @@
         "--unsetenv", "TMPDIR",
         "--dir", runDir,
         "--setenv", "XDG_RUNTIME_DIR", runDir,
+
+        // SFOS: /odm is a separate ext4 partition containing the Adreno GPU
+        // driver libraries.  "--dev-bind / /" does not recursively include
+        // this submount on kernel 4.14.  Bind it explicitly so the sandboxed
+        // WebProcess can load the GPU driver.
+        "--ro-bind", "/odm", "/odm",
+
+        // GPU firmware partition (vfat), needed by Adreno init.
+        "--ro-bind-try", "/vendor/firmware_mnt", "/vendor/firmware_mnt",
     };
 
     if (enableDebugPermissions()) {
